Thank you! I'm still new at this, so I suppose I need some pointers on setting research boundaries, but I'm happy to amend whatever needs amending.

I do realize it's fairly close to being a cliche, but I was hoping it was original enough to avoid it. I hadn't thought of what the scientific advances might eventually do, though- that's a possibility I'm not particularly comfortable with, now that I'm thinking about it.

It feels odd having to justify it, though. I've always felt like if you need to justify something, you didn't do a good enough job when you were making it… Still, I'll do what I can.







