17 Aug 2009 05:19






I like it. Two nits to pick though:

1. 960 depicts "three of the nine Muses", but lists a heretofore unknown Muse in addition to the nine commonly known. I suggest removing the "nine".

2. I think this should be Safe instead of Euclid. If you can take an object and put it in a room, and it doesn't do anything unless it's messed with, then it's Safe.

And I wouldn't worry too much about people adding crap to your article's research log— you can always take out any changes you don't like.







